14 WHEREAS, Reverend Reginald B. Newman was honored by the Atlanta Business Magazine
15 with the Atlanta Gospel Choice Award and named as one of the top 100 Influential Pastors
16 of Atlanta; and
17 WHEREAS, whether the task is preparing a sermon, visiting the sick, counseling the
18 troubled, baptizing a new believer, or acting as a theologian, educator, administrator, or
19 humanitarian, Reverend Reginald B. Newman has shown the energy, devotion, and
20 commitment truly reflective of divine guidance; and
21 WHEREAS, the unmatched spiritual assistance offered by Reverend Reginald B. Newman
22 is a source of strength and direction for persons in all walks of life; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper to recognize the outstanding accomplishments
24 of the dynamic Christian ministry of this devout and pious man.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body recognize and commend Reverend Reginald B. Newman on the
27 grand occasion of his retirement and extend best wishes for future health and happiness.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
30 Reverend Reginald B. Newman.
